BLACKSTONE WIND FARM LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Blackstone Wind Farm LLC ("Blackstone") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Blackstone generating facility ("Blackstone Facility").
The Blackstone Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in La Salle County, Illinois. The Blackstone Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Blackstone's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Blackstone Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Blackstone's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Blackstone shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $370,872.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $30,906.00
